snBgp4GenAlwaysCompareMed.name: snBgp4GenAlwaysCompareMed
snBgp4GenAlwaysCompareMed.description: To enable/disable the comparison of the Multi-Exit Discriminator for paths from neighbors in different AS.

snBgp4GenAutoSummary.name: snBgp4GenAutoSummary
snBgp4GenAutoSummary.description: To enable/disable the default behavior of automatic summarization of subnet routes into network-level routes.

snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference.name: snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference
snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference.description: To set the default local preference attribute.This is deprecated and snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference1 is introduced.

snBgp4GenDefaultInfoOriginate.name: snBgp4GenDefaultInfoOriginate
snBgp4GenDefaultInfoOriginate.description: To enable/disable the default Information Originate.

snBgp4GenFastExternalFallover.name: snBgp4GenFastExternalFallover
snBgp4GenFastExternalFallover.description: To enable/disable an action of immediately reset the BGP sessions of any directly adjacent external neighbors if the link used to reach them goes down.

snBgp4GenNextBootNeighbors.name: snBgp4GenNextBootNeighbors
snBgp4GenNextBootNeighbors.description: The next-boot configured number of neighbors in a BGP Peer Group. The minimum value of this MIB is snBgp4GenMinNeighbors. The maximum value of this MIB is snBgp4GenMaxNeighbors.

snBgp4GenNextBootRoutes.name: snBgp4GenNextBootRoutes
snBgp4GenNextBootRoutes.description: The next-boot configured number of Routes. The minimum value of this MIB is snBgp4GenMinRoutes. The maximum value of this MIB is snBgp4GenMaxRoutes.

snBgp4GenSynchronization.name: snBgp4GenSynchronization
snBgp4GenSynchronization.description: To enable/disable the synchronization between BGP and your IGP.

snBgp4GenTableMap.name: snBgp4GenTableMap
snBgp4GenTableMap.description: An octet string of the route-map name, each character of the name is represented by one octet.

snBgp4GenAdminStat.name: snBgp4GenAdminStat
snBgp4GenAdminStat.description: The administrative status of BGP4 in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the BGP4 routing is active in this router; 'disabled' disables BGP4 routing on this router.

snBgp4GenDefaultMetric.name: snBgp4GenDefaultMetric
snBgp4GenDefaultMetric.description: To set default metric values for the BGP4 protocol.This is deprecated and snBgp4GenDefaultMetric1 is introduced.

snBgp4GenMaxNeighbors.name: snBgp4GenMaxNeighbors
snBgp4GenMaxNeighbors.description: The maximum number of neighbors can be configured in a BGP Peer Group.

snBgp4GenMinNeighbors.name: snBgp4GenMinNeighbors
snBgp4GenMinNeighbors.description: The minimum number of neighbors can be configured in a BGP Peer Group.

snBgp4GenMaxRoutes.name: snBgp4GenMaxRoutes
snBgp4GenMaxRoutes.description: The maximum configured number of Routes.

snBgp4GenMinRoutes.name: snBgp4GenMinRoutes
snBgp4GenMinRoutes.description: The minimum configured number of Routes.

snBgp4GenMaxAddrFilters.name: snBgp4GenMaxAddrFilters
snBgp4GenMaxAddrFilters.description: The maximum configured number of BGP4 address filters.

snBgp4GenMaxAggregateAddresses.name: snBgp4GenMaxAggregateAddresses
snBgp4GenMaxAggregateAddresses.description: The maximum configured number of BGP4 aggregate addresses.

snBgp4GenMaxAsPathFilters.name: snBgp4GenMaxAsPathFilters
snBgp4GenMaxAsPathFilters.description: The maximum configured number of BGP4 AS-PATH filters.

snBgp4GenMaxCommunityFilters.name: snBgp4GenMaxCommunityFilters
snBgp4GenMaxCommunityFilters.description: The maximum configured number of BGP4 Community filters.

snBgp4GenMaxNetworks.name: snBgp4GenMaxNetworks
snBgp4GenMaxNetworks.description: The maximum configured number of BGP4 Networks.

snBgp4GenMaxRouteMapFilters.name: snBgp4GenMaxRouteMapFilters
snBgp4GenMaxRouteMapFilters.description: The maximum configured number of BGP4 Route-map Filters.

snBgp4GenNeighPrefixMinValue.name: snBgp4GenNeighPrefixMinValue
snBgp4GenNeighPrefixMinValue.description: The minimum configured value of BGP4 Neighbor Prefix.

snBgp4GenOperNeighbors.name: snBgp4GenOperNeighbors
snBgp4GenOperNeighbors.description: The current operational max number of neighbors configured for a BGP Group.

snBgp4GenOperRoutes.name: snBgp4GenOperRoutes
snBgp4GenOperRoutes.description: The current operational number of Routes.

snBgp4ExternalDistance.name: snBgp4ExternalDistance
snBgp4ExternalDistance.description: Administrative distance for BGP external routes.

snBgp4InternalDistance.name: snBgp4InternalDistance
snBgp4InternalDistance.description: Administrative distance for BGP internal routes.

snBgp4LocalDistance.name: snBgp4LocalDistance
snBgp4LocalDistance.description: Administrative distance for BGP local routes.

snBgp4OperNumOfAttributes.name: snBgp4OperNumOfAttributes
snBgp4OperNumOfAttributes.description: The operational number of attribute entries.

snBgp4NextBootMaxAttributes.name: snBgp4NextBootMaxAttributes
snBgp4NextBootMaxAttributes.description: The next boot maximum attribute entries. 10000 means reset to default.

snBgp4ClusterId.name: snBgp4ClusterId
snBgp4ClusterId.description: A cluster ID which is represented by 4 bytes unsigned integer (0..0xFFFFFFFF). 0 means reset to default.

snBgp4ClientToClientReflection.name: snBgp4ClientToClientReflection
snBgp4ClientToClientReflection.description: To enable/disable the client to client reflection in BGP4.

snBgp4GenTotalNeighbors.name: snBgp4GenTotalNeighbors
snBgp4GenTotalNeighbors.description: The current total number of neighbors running in a BGP Group.

snBgp4GenMaxPaths.name: snBgp4GenMaxPaths
snBgp4GenMaxPaths.description: The maximum configured number of Paths.

snBgp4GenConfedPeers.name: snBgp4GenConfedPeers
snBgp4GenConfedPeers.description: An AS number from 1 to 0xFFFF construct confederation peers. There are 50(max peers) of them. This integer number is represented by 2 OCTETs.

snBgp4GenDampening.name: snBgp4GenDampening
snBgp4GenDampening.description: The dampening of BGP4 in the router. value 'none' denotes that the BGP4 dampening is off 'parameters' denotes parameters are confibrurable. 'routeMap' denotes routemap is configurable.

snBgp4GenDampenMap.name: snBgp4GenDampenMap
snBgp4GenDampenMap.description: An octet string of the route-map name for dampening, each character of the name is represented by one octet.

snBgp4GenLocalAs4.name: snBgp4GenLocalAs4
snBgp4GenLocalAs4.description: BGP4 local autonomous system (AS) number to support 4 byte AS format.

snBgp4GenDefaultMetric1.name: snBgp4GenDefaultMetric1
snBgp4GenDefaultMetric1.description: To set default metric values for the BGP4 protocol.

snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference1.name: snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference1
snBgp4GenDefaultLocalPreference1.description: To set the default local preference attribute.

snBgp4AddrFilterEntry.name: snBgp4AddrFilterEntry
snBgp4AddrFilterEntry.description: An entry in the Bgp4 Address Filter table.

snBgp4AddrFilterIndex.name: snBgp4AddrFilterIndex
snBgp4AddrFilterIndex.description: The table index for a filter entry.

snBgp4AddrFilterAction.name: snBgp4AddrFilterAction
snBgp4AddrFilterAction.description: Action to take if the bgp address match with this filter.

snBgp4AddrFilterRowStatus.name: snBgp4AddrFilterRowStatus
snBgp4AddrFilterRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. Deleted rows go away immediately. The following values can be returned on reads: noSuch(0)...no such row invalid(1)...Setting it to 'invalid' has the effect of rendering it inoperative.. valid(2)....the row exists and is valid

snBgp4AggregateAddrOption.name: snBgp4AggregateAddrOption
snBgp4AggregateAddrOption.description: address(1), asSet(2), summaryOnly(3), the suppressMap(4), advertiseMap(5), attributeMap(6) are Options for creating an aggregate entry in a BGP routing table.

snBgp4AggregateAddrMap.name: snBgp4AggregateAddrMap
snBgp4AggregateAddrMap.description: This object associates with the snBgp4AggregateAddrOption and the suppressMap(4), advertiseMap(5), attributeMap(6) of the snBgp4AggregateAddrOption are only two Options for creating an aggregate address map. A SNMP-SET error will be returned for other options. An octet string of the map name, each character of the name is represented by one octet.

snBgp4CommunityFilterLocalAs.name: snBgp4CommunityFilterLocalAs
snBgp4CommunityFilterLocalAs.description: Send this route to peers in other sub-autonomous systems within the local confederation. Do not advertise this route to an external system.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgEntry.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgEntry
snBgp4NeighGenCfgEntry.description: An entry in the Bgp4 Community Filter table.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgNeighIp.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgNeighIp
snBgp4NeighGenCfgNeighIp.description: The IP Address for a neighbor entry.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgAdvertlevel.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgAdvertlevel
snBgp4NeighGenCfgAdvertlevel.description: To set the minimum interval between the sending of BGP routing updates.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgDefOriginate.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgDefOriginate
snBgp4NeighGenCfgDefOriginate.description: To enable/disable the default originate for this neighbor.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgEbgpMultihop.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgEbgpMultihop
snBgp4NeighGenCfgEbgpMultihop.description: To enable/disable the EBGP Muitihop for this neighbor.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgMaxPrefix.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgMaxPrefix
snBgp4NeighGenCfgMaxPrefix.description: To control how many prefixes can be received from a neighbor. The minimum value of the maximum prefix is snBgp4GenNeighPrefixMinValue. The maximum value of the maximum prefix is snBgp4GenOperRoutes.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgNextHopSelf.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgNextHopSelf
snBgp4NeighGenCfgNextHopSelf.description: To enable/disable the next-hop processing of BGP updates on the router.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgRemoteAs.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgRemoteAs
snBgp4NeighGenCfgRemoteAs.description: To specify a neighbor with an autonomous system number(AS).

snBgp4NeighGenCfgSendComm.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgSendComm
snBgp4NeighGenCfgSendComm.description: To specify that a COMMUNITES attribute should be sent to a BGP neighbor.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgWeight.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgWeight
snBgp4NeighGenCfgWeight.description: To assign a weight to a neighbor connection.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgWeightFilterList.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgWeightFilterList
snBgp4NeighGenCfgWeightFilterList.description: A number from 1 to 0xFFFF. There are 16 of them. This integer number is represented by 2 OCTETs.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgRowStatus.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgRowStatus
snBgp4NeighGenCfgRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete row in the table and control if they are used. The values that can be written are: delete(3)...deletes the row create(4)...creates a new row modify(5)...modifies an exsisting row applyDefault(6)...apply default value to an exsisting row If the row exists, then a SET with value of create(4) returns error 'badValue'. snBgp4NeighGenCfgUpdateSrcLpbIntf.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgUpdateSrcLpbIntf
snBgp4NeighGenCfgUpdateSrcLpbIntf.description: To allow internal BGP sessions to use any operational loopback interface (1..8) for TCP connections. Zero interface means to restore the interface assignment to the closest interface, which is called the best local address.

snBgp4NeighGenCfgRouteRefClient.name: snBgp4NeighGenCfgRouteRefClient
snBgp4NeighGenCfgRouteRefClient.description: To configure the router as a BGP route reflector, enable the specified neighbor as its client. When all the clients are disabled, the local router is no longer a route reflector.
